events.description: The Long Parliament of England is dissolved so as to prepare for the new Convention Parliament.

events.description: The Dutch bombard Givet during the Nine Years' War.
events.html: • 1696 – The Dutch bombard Givet during the Nine Years' War.[5]

events.description: King Gustav III of Sweden is shot; he dies on March 29.
events.html: • 1792 – King Gustav III of Sweden is shot; he dies on March 29.[6]

events.description: The Army Corps of Engineers is established to found and operate the United States Military Academy at West Point.
events.html: • 1802 – The Army Corps of Engineers is established to found and operate the United States Military Academy at West Point.

events.description: Prince Willem proclaims himself King of the United Kingdom of the Netherlands, the first constitutional monarch in the Netherlands.
events.html: • 1815 – Prince Willem proclaims himself King of the United Kingdom of the Netherlands, the first constitutional monarch in the Netherlands.

events.description: The Wanderers F.C. win the first FA Cup, the oldest football competition in the world, beating Royal Engineers A.F.C. 1–0 at The Oval in Kennington, London.
events.html: • 1872 – The Wanderers F.C. win the first FA Cup, the oldest football competition in the world, beating Royal Engineers A.F.C. 1–0 at The Oval in Kennington, London.

events.description: In Melbourne, the representatives of five colonies adopt a constitution, which would become the basis of the Commonwealth of Australia.[page needed]
events.html: • 1898 – In Melbourne, the representatives of five colonies adopt a constitution, which would become the basis of the Commonwealth of Australia.[7][page needed]

events.description: The 7th and 10th US cavalry regiments under John J. Pershing cross the US–Mexico border to join the hunt for Pancho Villa.
events.html: • 1916 – The 7th and 10th US cavalry regiments under John J. Pershing cross the US–Mexico border to join the hunt for Pancho Villa.

events.description: Finnish Civil War: Battle of Länkipohja is infamous for its bloody aftermath as the Whites execute 70–100 capitulated Reds.
events.html: • 1918 – Finnish Civil War: Battle of Länkipohja is infamous for its bloody aftermath as the Whites execute 70–100 capitulated Reds.

events.description: In accordance with the Treaty of Rome, Fiume becomes annexed as part of Italy.
events.html: • 1924 – In accordance with the Treaty of Rome, Fiume becomes annexed as part of Italy.

events.description: An earthquake (measuring around 7.0 magnitude) occurs in Dali, China, killing an estimated 5,000 people.
events.html: • 1925 – An earthquake (measuring around 7.0 magnitude) occurs in Dali, China, killing an estimated 5,000 people.[8]

events.description: History of Rocketry: Robert Goddard launches the first liquid-fueled rocket, at Auburn, Massachusetts.
events.html: • 1926 – History of Rocketry: Robert Goddard launches the first liquid-fueled rocket, at Auburn, Massachusetts.[9]

events.description: Adolf Hitler orders Germany to rearm herself in violation of the Treaty of Versailles. Conscription is reintroduced to form the Wehrmacht.
events.html: • 1935 – Adolf Hitler orders Germany to rearm herself in violation of the Treaty of Versailles. Conscription is reintroduced to form the Wehrmacht.

events.description: Warmer-than-normal temperatures rapidly melt snow and ice on the upper Allegheny and Monongahela rivers, leading to a major flood in Pittsburgh.
events.html: • 1936 – Warmer-than-normal temperatures rapidly melt snow and ice on the upper Allegheny and Monongahela rivers, leading to a major flood in Pittsburgh.

events.description: From Prague Castle, Hitler proclaims Bohemia and Moravia a German protectorate.
events.html: • 1939 – From Prague Castle, Hitler proclaims Bohemia and Moravia a German protectorate.

events.description: Operation Appearance takes place to re-establish British Somaliland
events.html: • 1941 – Operation Appearance takes place to re-establish British Somaliland[10]

events.description: World War II: The Battle of Iwo Jima ends, but small pockets of Japanese resistance persist.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: The Battle of Iwo Jima ends, but small pockets of Japanese resistance persist.

events.description: Ninety percent of Würzburg, Germany is destroyed in only 20 minutes by British bombers, resulting in at least 4,000 deaths.
events.html: • 1945 – Ninety percent of Würzburg, Germany is destroyed in only 20 minutes by British bombers, resulting in at least 4,000 deaths.[11]

entities.name: Bombing of Würzburg in World War II

events.description: Flying Tiger Line Flight 739 disappears in the western Pacific Ocean with all 107 aboard missing and presumed dead.
events.html: • 1962 – Flying Tiger Line Flight 739 disappears in the western Pacific Ocean with all 107 aboard missing and presumed dead.[12][13]

events.description: Launch of Gemini 8 with astronauts Neil Armstrong and David Scott. It would perform the first docking of two spacecraft in orbit.
events.html: • 1966 – Launch of Gemini 8 with astronauts Neil Armstrong and David Scott. It would perform the first docking of two spacecraft in orbit.[14]

events.description: Vietnam War: My Lai massacre occurs; between 347 and 500 Vietnamese villagers are killed by American troops.
events.html: • 1968 – Vietnam War: My Lai massacre occurs; between 347 and 500 Vietnamese villagers are killed by American troops.[15]

events.description: A Viasa McDonnell Douglas DC-9 crashes in Maracaibo, Venezuela, killing 155.
events.html: • 1969 – A Viasa McDonnell Douglas DC-9 crashes in Maracaibo, Venezuela, killing 155.[16][17]

events.description: Assassination of Kamal Jumblatt, the main leader of the anti-government forces in the Lebanese Civil War.
events.html: • 1977 – Assassination of Kamal Jumblatt, the main leader of the anti-government forces in the Lebanese Civil War.

events.description: Former Italian Prime Minister Aldo Moro is kidnapped; he is later murdered by his captors.
events.html: • 1978 – Former Italian Prime Minister Aldo Moro is kidnapped; he is later murdered by his captors.[18]

events.description: A Balkan Bulgarian Airlines Tupolev Tu-134 crashes near Gabare, Bulgaria, killing 73.
events.html: • 1978 – A Balkan Bulgarian Airlines Tupolev Tu-134 crashes near Gabare, Bulgaria, killing 73.[19]

events.description: Supertanker Amoco Cadiz splits in two after running aground on the Portsall Rocks, three miles off the coast of Brittany, resulting in the largest oil spill in history at that time.
events.html: • 1978 – Supertanker Amoco Cadiz splits in two after running aground on the Portsall Rocks, three miles off the coast of Brittany, resulting in the largest oil spill in history at that time.[20]

events.description: Sino-Vietnamese War: The People's Liberation Army crosses the border back into China, ending the war.
events.html: • 1979 – Sino-Vietnamese War: The People's Liberation Army crosses the border back into China, ending the war.[21]

events.description: William Buckley, the CIA station chief in Lebanon, is kidnapped by Hezbollah; he later dies in captivity.
events.html: • 1984 – William Buckley, the CIA station chief in Lebanon, is kidnapped by Hezbollah; he later dies in captivity.[22]

events.description: Associated Press newsman Terry Anderson is taken hostage in Beirut; he is not released until December 1991.
events.html: • 1985 – Associated Press newsman Terry Anderson is taken hostage in Beirut; he is not released until December 1991.[23]

events.description: Iran–Contra affair: Lieutenant Colonel Oliver North and Vice Admiral John Poindexter are indicted on charges of conspiracy to defraud the United States.
events.html: • 1988 – Iran–Contra affair: Lieutenant Colonel Oliver North and Vice Admiral John Poindexter are indicted on charges of conspiracy to defraud the United States.[24]

events.html: • 1988 – Halabja chemical attack: The Kurdish town of Halabja in Iraq is attacked with a mix of poison gas and nerve agents on the orders of Saddam Hussein, killing 5,000 people and injuring about 10,000 people.[25]

events.description: The Troubles: Ulster loyalist militant Michael Stone attacks a Provisional IRA funeral in Belfast with pistols and grenades. Three persons, one of them a member of PIRA are killed, and more than 60 others are wounded.
events.html: • 1988 – The Troubles: Ulster loyalist militant Michael Stone attacks a Provisional IRA funeral in Belfast with pistols and grenades. Three persons, one of them a member of PIRA are killed, and more than 60 others are wounded.
